		text = [[Left to themselves, most armies will fall dormant to minimize energy and maintenance requirements. With proper settings and their own nanolathe arrays, they can stay functional for a very long time. And they will leave enough sensors active to detect threats, then awaken and engage them until new orders or supervision are received.
 
Unfortunately, it seems I lack the proper identification codes to be recognized by most of those damn automata, or enough time to find a flaw in their code and hack them - so they are engaging me on sight. There may not be sapient minds behind them, but tactical AIs should not be underestimated, especially when they have the home advantage.
 
I will need to be careful, choose the time and place of battle, and not wait for reinforcements from everywhere on the planet to overwhelm me, but I can make it. Not that I have a choice...]]
